<li id="cite_note-35"><b><a href="#cite_ref-35" title="">^</a></b> This usage differs from usage in the <a href="/wiki/Authorized_King_James_Version" title="Authorized King James Version">Authorized King James Version</a> (Acts 17:29; Romans 1:20; and Colossians 2:9), where the term <i>Godhead</i> (godhood) was the word translators used for Greek words meaning deity or divinity. See <a href="/wiki/Godhead_(Christianity)" title="Godhead (Christianity)">Godhead (Christianity)</a>.</li>
